{
  "question_id": "e1b7f38c-c3e6-4058-8bf5-eb47c5216745",
  "short_text": "Inverted Right Angled Triangle",
  "content": "Write a program that reads a number `N` and prints an **Inverted Right Angled Triangle** of `N` rows using stars (`*`).\r\n\r\n```\r\n* * * * * \r\n* * * *\r\n* * *\r\n* *\r\n*\r\n```\r\n\r\n<MultiLineNote>\r\nThere is a space after every star.\r\n</MultiLineNote>\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Input\r\n\r\nThe input will be a single line containing an integer representing `N`.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Output\r\n\r\nThe output should be `N` rows containing stars (`*`) as an **Inverted Right Angled Triangle** shown in the sample output.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Explanation\r\n\r\nFor example, if the given number is `N = 5`,\r\n\r\n- Print the stars (`*`) on **5** rows as shown in the given image.\r\n\r\n<Img imageSrc='https://assets.ccbp.in/frontend/content/programming-foundations/cx-inverted-right-angled-triangle.png' widthPercent='70'/>\r\n\r\n<MultiLineNote>\r\nIn the given image, there is a space after every star.\r\n</MultiLineNote>\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\n* * * * * \r\n* * * * \r\n* * * \r\n* * \r\n* \r\n```",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "a26c7aea-e442-4128-8bbc-f85ff82e878f",
      "code_content": "n = int(input())\n\nfor i in range(n):\n    no_of_stars = n - i \n    row = \"* \" * no_of_stars \n    print(row)",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
  ],
